============================================================
  DISEASES & MEDICINE
============================================================

Disease:     Malaria
Type:        Parasitic
Pathogen:    Plasmodium falciparum
Transmission:Mosquito bite
Symptoms:    Fever, chills, sweating cycles
Treatment:   Artemisinin combination therapy
Deaths/yr:   0.619M
Vaccine:     Yes (RTS,S approved 2021)
Discovered:  1880

Disease:     Ebola
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    Ebola virus
Transmission:Bodily fluids contact
Symptoms:    Fever, bleeding, organ failure
Treatment:   Monoclonal antibodies, supportive
Deaths/yr:   0.001M
Vaccine:     Yes (Ervebo for Zaire strain)
Discovered:  1976

Disease:     COVID-19
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    SARS-CoV-2
Transmission:Respiratory droplets
Symptoms:    Fever, cough, loss of smell
Treatment:   Antivirals, supportive care
Deaths/yr:   5.0M
Vaccine:     Yes (mRNA vaccines)
Discovered:  2019

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

Concept:    Opportunity Cost
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Value of next-best alternative foregone when choosing
Formula:    OC = forgone alternative value
Economist:  Bastiat
Example:    Studying means forgoing wages you could have earned working

Concept:    Diminishing Returns
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: More of one input eventually yields smaller output increases
Formula:    Marginal product falls
Economist:  Turgot/Marshall
Example:    More workers in fixed factory eventually get in each other's way

